message.content:
We must “build” the current‐liability item by gathering those transactions that “create a payable” – that is, those purchase transactions that have an “Unpaid” status (with payment method “Account Payable” in our data). (Note that the “initial” entries were investments and fixed assets; no payables are recorded at the beginning so the “initial liabilities” are zero.)

For example, in our data the “Purchase” rows include many entries. Only those rows with Payment/receipt status “Unpaid” are recorded as a liability (the “Paid” ones have already been settled). (Other kinds of transactions – expenses, sales or interest receivables – do not add to accounts payable.) 

Going through the list we find the following “Purchase” rows (by their id) and recorded amounts that are unpaid:

• Purchase20231231002 – 829,440.00  
• Purchase20231231004 – 1,250,000.00  
• Purchase20231231005 – 246,000.00  
• Purchase20231231007 – 140,800.00  
• Purchase20231231008 – 254,320.00  
• Purchase20231231011 – 540,000.00  
• Purchase20231231013 – 585,000.00  
• Purchase20231231014 – 755,000.00  
• Purchase20231231015 – 59,850.00  
• Purchase20231231019 – 32,850.00  
• Purchase20231231022 – 19,050.00  
• Purchase20231231023 – 358,500.00  
• Purchase20231231024 – 402,000.00

Adding these in order gives:

 829,440.00  
+ 1,250,000.00 = 2,079,440.00  
+ 246,000.00 = 2,325,440.00  
+ 140,800.00 = 2,466,240.00  
+ 254,320.00 = 2,720,560.00  
+ 540,000.00 = 3,260,560.00  
+ 585,000.00 = 3,845,560.00  
+ 755,000.00 = 4,600,560.00  
+ 59,850.00 = 4,660,410.00  
+ 32,850.00 = 4,693,260.00  
+ 19,050.00 = 4,712,310.00  
+ 358,500.00 = 5,070,810.00  
+ 402,000.00 = 5,472,810.00

That is the total “unpaid accounts payable” at period‐end.

Because none of the “initial” transactions creates a liability (they are cash deposits, bank deposits and fixed asset purchases), the beginning value of current liabilities is 0.00.

Thus, our answer is:

--------------------------------------------------

{
  "solution": {
     "Total Current Liabilities Initial Value": "0.00",
     "Total Current Liabilities End Value": "5472810.00"
  }
}

This is the result for the current‐liabilities item for the balance sheet based on the provided transactions.
